    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Performance Breakdown</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>AI Autofocus Technology</h3>
        <p>
          The A6700's autofocus is borrowed from Sony's flagship A7R V and A1. The dedicated AI processing unit analyzes the scene 60 times per second, recognizing subjects and predicting motion. For birds in flight, it tracks the eye even as the bird weaves through branches. For cars, it locks onto the driver's helmet.
        </p>
        <p>
          Real-time Eye AF works on humans and animals (dogs, cats, birds). The camera finds eyes automatically and sticks to them even in chaotic scenes. For wildlife, portraits, and sports, this is the most advanced AF system in any APS-C camera. It's legitimately pro-level.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
        <p>
          4K60 is oversampled from the full 6K sensor readout, delivering exceptional sharpness and detail. 10-bit 4:2:2 internal recording gives serious color grading flexibility. S-Log3 and S-Cinetone profiles match Sony's cinema line (FX3, FX6) for consistent color workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          4K120 is a headline feature. It crops 1.58x (still usable) and delivers stunning slow-motion for B-roll. Active stabilization mode (digital+IBIS) provides gimbal-smooth handheld footage with a slight crop. For YouTube, commercials, and corporate video, the A6700 is a powerhouse.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Hybrid Performance</h3>
        <p>
          The 26MP sensor strikes a perfect balance: enough resolution for cropping and large prints, but not so many pixels that low-light suffers. ISO 6400 is clean; ISO 12,800 is usable. The 5.5-stop IBIS enables sharp handheld shots down to 1/4 second with stabilized lenses.
        </p>
        <p>
          11fps burst with full autofocus tracking is excellent for action. The buffer holds 1000+ JPEGs or 200+ RAW framesâ€”you won't fill it in real-world shooting. For weddings, events, and sports, the A6700 delivers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Build & Usability</h3>
        <p>
          The fully articulating screen is a huge upgrade over previous A6xxx models (which had tilting screens). Vlogging, overhead shots, and low-angle video all benefit. The magnesium alloy body is weather-sealed against dust and moistureâ€”you can shoot in rain or snow confidently.
        </p>
        <p>
          Dual SD card slots provide backup security. The FZ100 battery lasts ~570 shots or 90 minutes of 4K recording. Menu system is Sony's latest (much improved over older models). Overall, it's a professional tool in a compact package.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

