        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              Should I get the A6700 or upgrade to full-frame?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
            <p>
              If you want compact size and lighter lenses, the A6700 is brilliant. Full-frame (A7 IV, A7C II) gives better low-light and shallower depth-of-field, but costs more and weighs more. For travel, wildlife, and YouTube, APS-C is often ideal. The A6700 has flagship features at 60% the cost.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              Can I use full-frame E-mount lenses on the A6700?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
            <p>
              Yes! All Sony FE lenses work on the A6700 (with 1.5x crop factor). This is great for lens investmentâ€”if you upgrade to full-frame later, your lenses carry over. Native APS-C lenses are smaller/lighter, but FE lenses give more options.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
